# WOBBLE OS build context — DENY BY DEFAULT.
#
# The image must contain ONLY the inputs the Next standalone build + the drizzle migrator stage
# need. Everything else — machine-local `storage/` media, design zips, videos, docs, tests, e2e
# fixtures, logs, .env* secrets, audit artifacts — is excluded, and NEW top-level files are excluded
# unless explicitly allow-listed below. This is the fix for WOB-AUD-002: image contents no longer
# depend on what happens to sit in the working tree, and local business media can never be embedded
# in a pushed image. `scripts/check-docker-image.mjs` re-verifies the built image against a denylist.
*

# --- Allow-list: exactly the build inputs ---
!package.json
!package-lock.json
!next.config.ts
!next-env.d.ts
!tsconfig.json
!drizzle.config.ts
!src
!public
!scripts

# --- Defense in depth: re-exclude nested non-runtime material under allow-listed dirs ---
**/node_modules
**/.next
**/*.log
**/.DS_Store
**/.env
**/.env.*
scripts/*.sh
